neutral.name: Neutral Space
neutral.desc: This space can be freely traversed and have no additional effects.

shop.name: Shop
shop.desc: A player who lands on this space receives a random item, if there is room in the player's inventory.

altar.name: Altar
altar.desc: A player on this space is allowed to make one wish. At the end of the turn, all players who made wishes have their wishes granted and then are returned to Start. Multiple players on this space do not engage in combat. Emits light level 5. In lieu of making a wish, a player who lands on this space can instead voluntarily be teleported to the Molten Core of the World at a random position.

start.name: Start Square
start.desc: All new players start on this square. Players sharing this space do not fight, and any player on this space does not lose HP for any reason. A player who ends his turn on Start is cured of any status ailments.

gap.name: Empty Gap
gap.desc: These spaces are ordinarily impassible to players. If a player is forced onto a gap, they immediately return to Start and loses 5 HP. A player who is adjacent to a gap can choose to leap into the gap.

giver.name: Silver Giver
giver.desc: Anyone on this space at the end of the turn receives a Silver Coin.

black.name: Darkness
black.desc: A space shrouded in darkness; you can't tell what it is from this distance.

highway.name: Speed Highway
highway.visual: light blue space with dark blue 'interstate' sign
highway.desc: This space is always considered adjacent to its paired Speed Highway space. Players standing on one of the two may expend one movement point to move to the other.

grass.name: Grass
grass.desc: This space behaves like a neutral space but cannot become tainted. At the end of the turn, if this tile has fewer than two grass tiles adjacent or diagonally-adjacent to it, it becomes a dirt tile. If this tile has more than three grass tiles adjacent or diagonally-adjacent to it, it becomes a Tree Space.

dirt.name: Dirt
dirt.desc: This space behaves like a neutral space. At the end of the turn, if a dirt tile is surrounded (adjacent or diagonally) by either 2 or 3 grass tiles, it becomes a grass tile. Alternatively, if a dirt tile is adjacent or diagonally-adjacent to a water tile, the dirt becomes a grass tile.

tree.name: Tree Space
tree.visual: teal space with green tree clipart
tree.desc: Light passing through this space is diminished by one. Moving onto this space costs two movement points. Tree Spaces cannot be tainted, and they cure the tainted status on adjacent and diagonally-adjacent spaces. At the end of the turn, if this tile has one or fewer grass tiles adjacent to it, it becomes a grass tile.

water.name: Water Space
water.desc: A player who moves onto this space must stop here. This space is always Fireproof.

tneutral.name: Tainted Neutral Space
tneutral.visual: empty gray space with tainted border
tneutral.desc: This space requires 2 movement points to move onto. This space is Tainted.

yeolde.name: Ye Olde Shoppe
yeolde.desc: A player who is on this space can exchange any coins for random items. The following currency types are not accepted: ruthenium, rhodium, palladium, osmium, iridium, platinum, and gold. A player does not have to stop on this space to exchange.

fire.name: Fire Space
fire.visual: greenish space with Fire on it
fire.desc: Anyone who passes this space takes damage equal to their ATK power. Emits light level 2. At the beginning of each turn, every Fire Space spreads to all adjacent spaces, lighting them on fire as well. If this Fire Space is adjacent to one or more Fire Spaces before this effect triggers, then this Fire Space spreads twice as far. This doubling effect does NOT stack. If this space exists for more than one full turn, it is transported to the Molten Core of the World. The previous position of the Fire Space is replaced by an Ash Space.

stair.name: Staircase
stair.visual: light gray space with black stairway outline on it
stair.desc: Anyone who occupies this space can spend one movement point to move to the same position either up or down one floor. Players may not move onto floors which do not exist.

ash.name: Ash Space
ash.desc: You must spend 2 movement points to move through this space. Adjacent Grass, Tree, and Water tiles spread to this space. Ash Spaces cannot catch fire, and there is a 33% chance each turn that the Ash Space will become dirt.

trollden.name: Troll Den
trollden.desc: Passively spawns Trolls until there are as many Trolls on the board as there are Troll Dens. If no Spyglass exists on the board, one of the spawned Trolls has a Spyglass.

twater.name: Tainted Water Space
twater.visual: blue space with watery texture and tainted border
twater.desc: A player who moves onto this space must stop here. This space is Tainted. A player who stops here has a 10% chance of instantly drowning and being sent back to Start. This does not count as a death. This space is always Fireproof.

tdirt.name: Tainted Dirt Space
tdirt.visual: solid brown space with tainted border
tdirt.desc: This space counts as a Dirt Space, for the purposes of terrain spread. If this space would transform into a Grass Space by the terrain rules, it turns into a Tainted Grass Space.

tgrass.name: Tainted Grass Space
tgrass.visual: green grass-textured space with tainted border
tgrass.desc: This space counts as a Grass Space, for the purposes of terrain spread. If this space would transform into a Dirt Space, it turns into a Tainted Dirt Space. If this space would transform into a Tree Space, it transforms into a Tainted Tree Space.

ttree.name: Tainted Tree Space
ttree.visual: teal space with green tree clipart and tainted border
ttree.desc: This space counts as a Tree Space, for the purposes of terrain spread. This space will not turn back into grass as a result of terrain mechanics. It costs two movement points to move onto this space. Diminishes light by 1. When a player moves onto this space, there's a 25% chance that the evil tainted tree will grab the player by the roots, forcing them to stop on this space for the turn and take 1 damage. Adjacent Tree Spaces will become Tainted by this space. Tainted trees are made of dead wood and are always fireproof.

ttrollden.name: Tainted Troll Den
ttrollden.visual: space with troll image and tainted texture
ttrollden.desc: Passively spawns Trolls every turn, regardless of the number of Troll Den spaces.

spyglass.name: Spyglass
spyglass.desc: Usable once per turn. Select a space anywhere on the board. You privately learn its true identity, even if the space had hidden information or was concealed by darkness.

deathwhistle.name: Death Whistle
deathwhistle.desc: Usable once per turn, when you're on the same space as another player. Death is summoned to the current space, and the chosen player is required to challenge them to a game immediately. This item has no effect if there is no Death character on the board.

item.name: Item
item.desc: Icon used to represent items on the map.

goldcoin.name: Gold Coin
goldcoin.desc: Can be picked up by a player. Always protected from wishes. Emits light level 1.

silvercoin.name: Silver Coin
silvercoin.desc: Can be picked up by a player. These are like gold coins, but are not protected by the game's rules and have no intrinsic value. Emits light level 1.

war.name: War
war.desc: Moves randomly each turn, attacking any player or other token who ends up on the same space. Permanently gains 1 ATK whenever he successfully kills anyone. If he dies, War respawns on a random space the following turn, with his ATK reset to 1. All adjacent and diagonally-adjacent spaces to this token become Fireproof. If a Fire Space is extinguished by this effect, this token gets paid a Sulfur Coin. The inventory of this token is hidden from players.

famine.name: Famine
famine.desc: Moves randomly each turn. If he ends up on the same space as another player, Famine rots one food- or drink- themed item in that player's inventory at random. All adjacent and diagonally-adjacent spaces to this token become Fireproof. If a Fire Space is extinguished by this effect, this token gets paid a Sulfur Coin. The inventory of this token is hidden from players.

pestilence.name: Pestilence
pestilence.desc: Moves randomly each turn. At the end of the turn, whatever space Pestilence lands on becomes tainted. All adjacent and diagonally-adjacent spaces to this token become Fireproof. If a Fire Space is extinguished by this effect, this token gets paid a Sulfur Coin. The inventory of this token is hidden from players.

death.name: Death
death.desc: Moves randomly each turn. If he lands on the same space as a player, that player may challenge Death to a deadly game of dice. If the player wins the game of chance, he gets a random useful item. If the player loses, he dies. All adjacent and diagonally-adjacent spaces to this token become Fireproof. If a Fire Space is extinguished by this effect, this token gets paid a Sulfur Coin. The inventory of this token is hidden from players.

troll.name: Troll
troll.desc: Moves randomly each turn, avoiding landing on the same space as another Troll. When a non-Troll token (including a player) passes a Troll, they may offer the Troll a shiny object (such as a coin). If they refuse or cannot, then they must stop on the Troll's space. A Troll which was just bribed with a shiny object will not provoke combat from the token which bribed it. When a Troll dies, it drops any gold coins it had at random locations, and the Spyglass (if it had one) on its death square. All other items the Troll owned are lost. Does not emit light.

lion.name: Lion Cracker
lion.desc: Chases the nearest player each turn. Moves randomly if there are no players nearby. Produces light level 1.

zebra.name: Zebra Cracker
zebra.desc: Moves randomly each turn, trying to avoid players whenever possible.

tiger.name: Tiger Cracker
tiger.desc: Chases the nearest player each turn. Moves randomly if there are no players nearby. Produces light level 1.

gorilla.name: Gorilla Cracker
gorilla.desc: Moves randomly each turn. If attacked, the Gorilla Cracker will change course and pursue its most recent attacker until they're dead.

raft.name: Raft
raft.desc: Doesn't move, attack, or do anything on its own. If a player shares a space with the Raft, that player does not have to stop on the Water space and can continue moving, dragging the Raft with them. If multiple tokens are on the Raft, then all tokens sharing a space with the Raft are carried with it. The Raft cannot leave the water.

ship.name: Ship
ship.desc: Moves randomly each turn, and can pass water with only one movement point. Must remain on the water. Each turn, the Ship will fire one or both of its cannons at a nearby tile. The Ship prefers to fire only one of its cannons. The first cannon is a party cannon, which leaves behind Confetti on the tile. The second cannon is a conventional cannon. It leaves a Cannonball behind and deals one damage to anything currently on the target space.

confetti.name: Confetti
confetti.desc: Players and other tokens can move onto a space containing Confetti without expending a movement point. If the Confetti is resting on a water space, then the water space leaves players entering it with one movement point, rather than completely stopping them. Confetti on a fire space is destroyed immediately. Confetti disappears after one full turn. Emits light level 1.

cannonball.name: Cannonball
cannonball.desc: A heavy ball. Any player who moves onto a space containing a Cannonball must expend one extra movement point doing so. A player on the same space as a Cannonball can toss the Cannonball to an adjacent space of their choosing, dealing one damage to everyone on that space at the time. A Cannonball landing in water or fire is destroyed. A Cannonball landing in an empty space falls all the way down to the Molten Core of the World. Does not emit light.

fireproof.name: Fireproof
fireproof.desc: This space can never be converted into a Fire Space. If this space is a Fire Space when it becomes Fireproof, it is replaced with a simple, non-Fire space at random.

immunityimmunity.name: Immunity Wish Immunity
immunityimmunity.desc: No further Immunity attributes may be added to this space.

radioimmunity.name: Radio Wish Immunity
radioimmunity.desc: Players can fight on this space, even if they don't have the same life count.

smolderingimmunity.name: Smoldering Wish Immunity
smolderingimmunity.desc: The equipped space can catch fire, even if it's an Ash Space. The equipped space cannot decay into a dirt space, even if it's an Ash Space.

seafaringimmunity.name: Seafaring Wish Immunity
seafaringimmunity.desc: A Ship, Raft, Cannonball, or Confetti on this space has no effect. Rafts cannot be ridden, Ships cannot fire their cannons (though they can still move), Cannonballs and Confetti do not have any effect and will not despawn.

fireimmunity.name: Fire Wish Immunity
fireimmunity.desc: A Fire Space affected by this does not deal damage to a player passing it. A Fire Space affected by this does not emit light.

decayimmunity.name: Decay Wish Immunity
decayimmunity.desc: If this space is tainted, it will not decay back to normal.

rulings.desc: Any Altar wishes occur at the end of the turn, after all player movement is completed.
Effects which target a stat that a token lacks have no effect on the token. For example, a space that deals damage will not affect a token who has no concept of HP.

The specific nature of combat in the case of tokens which are deficient in some stats is this. All involved players or tokens who have an ATK stat will attack all involved players or tokens who have an HP stat. All such attacks happen simultaneously, and in general a token will never attack itself unless otherwise stated.

In general, an action which attempts to move into a gap is considered to be a mistake or a typo, and the player will not be allowed to move into the gap. If the movement into the gap was intentional, this should be specified in the post. This ruling does not apply if the player in question has any equipment that would enable him or her to pass the gaps without the normal penalty.

The larger the magnitude of a wish, the less likely it is to end up in the wisher's favor. That is, a simple wish is likely to go exactly as intended. A large and complicated wish may be interpreted extremely literally and the results may not be what was desired.
